narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: basic laboratory skills for general chemistry (spectrophotometry, titrations, kinetics, buffers, etc.), reinforced concepts learned in lecture, use of laboratory equipment
I furthered my insight into the techniques, equipment, and processes in a chemistry lab.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
strengths: a lot of resources for preparation, plenty of opportunities to ask questions, thorough explanations and pre-lab lectures, interesting experiments

weaknesses: pre-lab quizzes are not always easy even with thorough preparation, lab reports are difficult and time-consuming but are manageable with collaboration and asking questions, easy to lose small points so you have to be very careful, no clear rubric for lab reports

Strengths:
1 on 1 teaching 
Pre-Lab Videos
Pre-Lab Lectures 
Ability to speak with professor

Weaknesses:
N/A

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, I would. This course is foundational for any science student and a requirement for many science majors. The skills are critical and the content is interesting as it connects to the lecture course and is relevant in the real world. It is also an opportunity to get familiar with working in a lab.
I most certainly would if said student wishes to endeavor to further their insight and knowledge in the discipline of chemistry.

Yes, Dr. G is very helpful towards students and its clear he really loves teaching. He will go above and beyond to explain concepts and help with lab reports. The prelab quizzes were difficult, and summer courses are never easy to do. However, as far as summer courses go, it was good.

narratives.question_text: The Canvas course site allowed me to identify and access required course materials easily.
How will you use the knowledge and skills you learned in this course in your future endeavors?
comments: I will use general chemistry knowledge as well as lab skills as I pursue biology and medicine. Also, I am now more comfortable with lab equipment and procedures which will be useful in the future
I will use the skills I learned in the lab as far as techniques go, and learned how to write concise, promising lab reports.
